Screenshot: Google Maps Google Map is known a web mapping services developed by the tech giant Google to give direction to its users. It also shows the panoramic views of streets and real-time traffic condition. But in the case of a Peruvian man, he divorced his wife after Google Map showed his wife publicly displaying affection for another man. The Peruvian man was searching for a short route to a popular bridge in Lima, the capital of Peru when he spotted a familiar figure on the Google Street view photos. He later identified the familiar figure in the picture as his wife, who was stroking another man hair.
The photo was taken by Google camera car at Puente de Los Suspiros de Barranco in Lima 2013. The Peruvian man reacted to this and shared it on Facebook.